config BR2_PACKAGE_PANICOS_SWAY
	bool "panicos-sway"
	depends on BR2_INIT_SYSTEMD
	depends on BR2_PACKAGE_SWAY
	help
	  Kiosk-mode Sway compositor configuration for PanicOS launcher
	  flavors. Provides:

	    /etc/sway/panicos-kiosk.conf — minimal config: hide cursor,
	      no decorations, no idle, exec the foreground app.
	    sway.service — systemd unit that brings sway up before
	      EmulationStation (or any other Wayland client).

	  Mirrors the ROCKNIX/JELOS approach: sway runs as the display
	  manager, ES connects as a Wayland client. Without sway in this
	  shape, ES on KMSDRM has visible layering jank on menus and
	  overlays — sway does the layer-shell composition that ES
	  itself doesn't.
